  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2061",
  "title": "react-instantsearch triggers unnecessary requests when everything is unmounted",
  "body": "Hello everybody,\r\n\r\nWhen all react-instantsearch components/widgets are unmounted (for instance, in case of route change), many unnecessary search requests are triggered by react-instantsearch. The below fiddle triggers an unmounting of the whole tree below the `InstantSearch` component after 1s.\r\n\r\nSteps:\r\n1. Open https://jsfiddle.net/uza8mda0/1/\r\n1. Open network tab, filter for XHR requests\r\n1. Click `play` button, wait for >= 1s\r\n1. Observe that 4 requests have been triggered in total, instead of one.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the current behavior?** Unnecessary requests are triggered when everything is unmounted, even with cache enabled on the algolia client\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the expected behavior?** Unmounting everything doesn't trigger any request.\r\n\r\n**What project are you opening an issue for?**\r\n- react-instantsearch\r\n\r\n**What is the version you are using? Always use the latest one before opening a bug issue.** 3.2.1\r\n\r\n",
